name: CompareTo
desc: Compares the date to another date.

name: Day
desc: Returns the day of the date.

name: Hour
desc: Returns the hour of the date.

name: IsUtc
desc: Returns true if the date is UTC.

name: Millisecond
desc: Returns the millisecond of the date.

name: Minute
desc: Returns the minute of the date.

name: Month
desc: Returns the month of the date.

name: Second
desc: Returns the second of the date.

name: TimeZoneName
desc: Returns the time zone name of the date.

name: TimeZoneOffset
desc: Returns the time zone offset of the date.

name: Weekday
desc: Returns the weekday of the date.

name: Year
desc: Returns the year of the date.

name: registerDateExtensions
desc:
Registers all date extensions.
These are registered automatically by the VM.

name: clock
desc: Provides a clock() function that returns the current time in milliseconds since the epoch.

name: date
desc: Provides a date() function that creates a DateTime object from the given arguments.

name: defineVmNativeFunctions
desc:
This registers all the built-in native functions.
This is called automatically when by the VM.

name: duration
desc: Provides a duration() function that creates a Duration object from the given arguments.

name: jsonDecode
desc:
Provides a jsonDecode() function that decodes a JSON string to a map object.
Supports conversion of DateTime objects from strings.

name: jsonEncode
desc:
Provides a jsonEncode() function that encodes a map object to a JSON string.
Supports conversion of DateTime objects to strings.

name: now
desc: Provides a now() function that returns the current time.

name: parseDateTime
desc: Provides a parseDateTime() function that parses a date string to a DateTime object.

name: quit
desc:
Provides a quit() function that immediately halts script execution and exits
with the given return code.

name: rndDouble
desc: Provides a rndDouble() function that returns a random double value.

name: rndInt
desc: Provides a rndInt() function that returns a random integer value.

name: wait
desc: Provides a wait() function that returns a Future that completes after the given number of milliseconds.

name: Abs
desc: Returns the absolute value of the duration.

name: CompareTo
desc:
Compares the duration to another duration and returns the result of the comparison.
Returns 0 if the durations are equal, a negative number if the duration is less than
the other duration, and a positive number if the duration is greater than the other duration.

name: InHours
desc: Returns the number of hours in the duration.

name: InMilliseconds
desc: Returns the number of milliseconds in the duration.

name: InMinutes
desc: Returns the number of minutes in the duration.

name: InSeconds
desc: Returns the number of seconds in the duration.

name: InYears
desc: Returns the number of years in the duration.

name: IsNegative
desc: Returns true if the duration is negative.

name: registerDurationExtensions
desc:
Registers native methods for the Duration type.
These are registere automatically by the VM.

name: AddAll
desc: Adds all elements from the provided list to the target list.

name: Any
desc: Returns true if any element in the list satisfies the provided test function.

name: Clear
desc: Clears the list.

name: Contains
desc: Returns true if the list contains the provided element.

name: Every
desc: Returns true if all elements in the list satisfy the provided test function.

name: Filter
desc: Returns a new list containing only the elements that satisfy the provided test function.

name: Fold
desc: Reduces the list to a single value by applying the provided function to each element.

name: ForEach
desc:
Iterates over the list elements and calls the provided function for each element.
The function should take one argument: element.

name: Head
desc: Returns the first element of the list.

name: IndexOf
desc: Returns the index of the first occurrence of the provided element in the list.

name: IsEmpty
desc: Returns true if the list is empty.

name: IsNotEmpty
desc: Returns true if the list is not empty.

name: Join
desc: Joins the elements of the list into a string using the provided separator.

name: Length
desc: Returns the number of elements in the list.

name: Map
desc: Returns a new list containing the results of applying the provided function to each element.

name: RemoveAt
desc: Removes the element at the specified index.

name: RemoveWhere
desc: Removes all elements from the list that satisfy the provided test function.

name: Reversed
desc: Returns a new list with the elements in reverse order.

name: Sort
desc: Sorts the list using the provided comparison function.

name: Tail
desc: Returns a new list containing all elements except the first.

name: ToString
desc: Returns a string representation of the list.

name: registerListExtensions
desc:
Registers all list extensions.
This is called automatically by the VM.

name: Clear
desc: Clears all entries from the map.

name: ContainsKey
desc: Returns true if the map contains the specified key.

name: ContainsValue
desc: Returns true if the map contains the specified value.

name: ForEach
desc:
Iterates over the map entries and calls the provided function for each entry.
The function should take two arguments: the key and the value.

name: IsEmpty
desc: Returns true if the map is empty.

name: IsNotEmpty
desc: Returns true if the map is not empty.

name: Keys
desc: Returns a list of the map's keys.

name: Length
desc: Returns the number of entries in the map.

name: Merge
desc: Merges the specified map into this map.

name: Remove
desc: Removes the entry with the specified key from the map.

name: ToString
desc: Returns a string representation of the map.  Simply printing a map yields the same result.

name: Values
desc: Returns a list of the map's values.

name: registerMapExtensions
desc:
Registers all native methods for the Map type.
This is called automatically by the VM.

name: Abs
desc: Returns the absolute value of this number.

name: Acos
desc: Returns the arccosine of this number.

name: Asin
desc: Returns the arcsine of this number.

name: Atan
desc: Returns the arctangent of this number.

name: Atan2
desc: Returns the arctangent of this number and another number.

name: Ceil
desc: Returns the ceiling value of this number.

name: CompareTo
desc: Compares this number with another number.

name: Exp
desc: Returns the exponential of this number.

name: Floor
desc: Returns the floor value of this number.

name: IsEven
desc: Returns true if this number is even.

name: IsOdd
desc: Returns true if this number is odd.

name: Log
desc: Returns the natural logarithm of this number.

name: Max
desc: Returns the maximum of this number and another number.

name: Min
desc: Returns the minimum of this number and another number.

name: Mod
desc: Returns the remainder of this number divided by another number.

name: Pow
desc: Raises this number to the power of another number.

name: Round
desc: Rounds this number to the nearest integer.

name: Sqrt
desc: Returns the square root of this number.

name: Tan
desc: Returns the tangent of this number.

name: ToString
desc: Returns the string representation of this number.

name: Truncate
desc: Returns the truncated value of this number.

name: registerNumberExtensions
desc:
Registers all number extensions.
These are registered automatically by the VM.

name: DartFunctionCallback
desc: Defines a signature for a callback function that handles dart() function calls at runtime.

name: IncludesPreprocesser
desc:
A base class for "includes" preprocessers.  Includes preprocessers are used to returns a list of files to include in the
source code file before it is compiled.  This allows for some platform specific preprocessing.

name: getLibraries
desc: Returns a map of files to be included in the compilation process.

name: getLibraryNamesToInclude
desc:
A helper method that parses the source code and returns a list of library names to include.
This method should not be overridden.

name: NativeFunction
desc: Defines a signature for a native function.

name: NativeMethodDefinition
desc: Defines a native method that can be registered with the VM.

name: NativeMethodFunction
desc: Defines the signature of a native method function.

name: NativeMethodTarget
desc: Enumerates the types of objects that can have native methods registered.

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: ObjClosure
desc:
Defines a closure object, which is used by the VM at runtime to
execute a function with its enclosing environment.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: OutCallback
desc: Defines a signature for a callback function that handles out() function calls at runtime.

name: ParseError
desc: Represents a parsing error during code compilation

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: RuntimeError
desc: Represents a runtime error during script execution.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: compileAndRun
desc: Compiles and runs the given OcheScript source code.

name: registerNativeFunction
desc: Registers a native function to extend the language capabilities.

name: registerNativeMethod
desc: Registers a native method to extend the language capabilities.

name: CodeUnitAt
desc: Returns the code unit at the specified index.

name: CompareTo
desc:
Compares the string to another string and returns the result of the comparison.
Returns 0 if the strings are equal, a negative number if the string is less than the other string, and a positive number if the string is greater than the other string.

name: Contains
desc: Returns true if the string contains the specified substring.

name: Head
desc: Returns the first character of the string.

name: IsEmpty
desc: Returns true if the string is empty.

name: IsLowerCase
desc: Returns true if all letters in the string are lowercase, ignoring non-alphabetic characters.

name: IsNotEmpty
desc: Returns true if the string is not empty.

name: IsUpperCase
desc: Returns true if all letters in the string are uppercase, ignoring non-alphabetic characters.

name: Length
desc: Returns the length of the string.

name: ReplaceAll
desc: Replaces all occurrences of a specified substring with another substring.

name: Split
desc: Splits the string into a list of substrings separated by the specified separator.

name: SubString
desc: Returns a new string that is a substring of the original string.

name: Tail
desc: Returns a new string that is the original string without its first character.

name: ToLower
desc: Returns a new string that is the original string in lowercase.

name: ToUpper
desc: Returns a new string that is the original string in uppercase.

name: Trim
desc: Returns a new string with leading and trailing whitespace removed.

name: registerStringExtensions
desc:
Registers all string extensions.
This is called automatically by the VM.

name: WindowsPlatformPreProcessor
desc: OcheScript Includes Preprocessor for windows platform.

name: getLibraries
desc: Returns a list of files to be included in the compilation process.
